---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Shandapha Pricing"
  description="Free stays shippable. Premium sells polish and speed. Business sells governance and rollout control."
>
  <section class="section">
    <span class="eyebrow">Trust-first pricing</span>
    <h1>Free is shippable. Premium sells speed. Business sells control.</h1>
    <p>
      The trust layer stays deterministic in every tier: contracts, semantic tokens, merge-safe
      patches, Doctor checks, and the portability baseline are not paywalled.
    </p>
    <div class="pricing-grid">
      <article class="plan">
        <strong>Free</strong>
        <p>Core tokens, runtime, primitives, WC baseline, React wrappers, starter templates, Quick Brand, Import Brand v1, patching, diff report, and Doctor baseline.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="plan featured">
        <strong>Premium</strong>
        <p>Glass and Neon packs, faster surface selection, premium polish, advanced DataTable flows, and more guided modernization convenience.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="plan">
        <strong>Business</strong>
        <p>Governance, approvals, usage, rollout control, auditability, org defaults, and continuity policies across teams and products.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
